  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to compare the effect of two drugs that can help in the
      prevention of regurgitation during the administration of enteral nutrition and define which
      one is the most effective.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Two prokinetic drugs (metoclopramide and erythromycin) will be compared during the
      administration of enteral nutrition in critically ill patients. We would like to know which
      one is the most effective in preventing regurgitation and risk of aspiration, which is a
      common complication of enteral nutritional support. This will be evaluated by measuring
      gastric residue every six hours.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
